1. Initialize an empty string "readmeText" to store the generated readme content
2. Prompt the user for the project name, description, installation instructions, usage, contribution guidelines and license
3. Append the user inputs to "readmeText" in the following format:
   - Project name: as the title of the readme
   - Description: as a brief paragraph
   - Installation: as a subheading with bullet points
   - Usage: as a subheading with examples
   - Contribution: as a subheading with guidelines
   - License: as a subheading with the selected license
4. Write "readmeText" to a file named "README.md"
5. End program


